interfaces.transform.projection

Interface ProjectionInterface


  • public interface ProjectionInterface
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Learning Orchestra
    Summary:
    This interface is responsible for projection operations, i.e., dataset attribute insertion or removal, dataset reduction or enlargement, join two or more datasets, values update and many more.

    • Method Detail

      • removeDatasetAttributesSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject removeDatasetAttributesSync(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                                       java.lang.String datasetOldName,
                                                       java.util.Enumeration<java.lang.String> attributes,
                                                       boolean newDataset)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - represents the dataset name
        datasetOldName - represents the existing dataset name
        attributes - represents the set of attributes to be considered. The remaining attributes are deleted.
        newDataset - is a boolean responsible to inform if a new dataset will be created or not
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method eliminates some attributes of a dataset. It can create a new dataset or not. The removal operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • insertDatasetAttributeSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject insertDatasetAttributeSync(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                                      java.lang.String attribute,
                                                      java.lang.String existingAttribute,
                                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> values,
                                                      boolean newDataset)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - represents the dataset name
        attribute - represents the new attribute
        existingAttribute - represents an existing attribute of the dataset
        values - represents the set of values to be used. In this case, the existing attribute values are mapped into new values (key-value pair), this way the new attribute can receive multiple new values. For instance, the existing attribute sex with values male and female can be mapped into the new values A and B of the new attribute XYZ.
        newDataset - is a boolean responsible to inform if a new dataset will be created or not
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method inserts a single attributes into a dataset. It can create a new dataset or not. The attribute insertion operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • reduceDatasetSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject reduceDatasetSync(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                             int sizeReduction,
                                             boolean newDataset)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - is the name of the dataset
        sizeReduction - is the percentage of reduction. Example 10%, 20%, etc.
        newDataset - is a boolean responsible to inform if a new dataset will be created or not
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method reduces the original number of tuples/registers in a specific percentage. It can just randomly eliminates the tuples or it can adopt a more sophisticated strategy to reduce the dataset size. The dataset reduction operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • enlargeDatasetSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject enlargeDatasetSync(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                              int sizeEnlarge,
                                              boolean newDataset)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - is the name of the dataset
        sizeEnlarge - is the percentage of growth. Example 10%, 20%, 110%, etc.
        newDataset - is a boolean responsible to inform if a new dataset will be created or not
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method enlarges the original number of tuples/registers in a specific percentage. It can just randomly clones the tuples or it can adopt a more sophisticated strategy to enlarge the dataset size. The enlargement operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • joinDatasetsSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject joinDatasetsSync(java.util.Enumeration<java.lang.String> datasetNames,
                                            java.lang.String datasetName,
                                            boolean removeExistingDatasets)
        Parameters:
        datasetNames - represents the list of datasets to be joined
        datasetName - represents the name of the new dataset
        removeExistingDatasets - is a boolean indicating if the existing datasets must be removed. If true one of the datasets can be used to join the others.
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method joins two or more datasets into a single one. They must have the same attributes. The join operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • joinDatasetsSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject joinDatasetsSync(java.lang.String datasetNameOne,
                                            java.lang.String datasetNameTwo,
                                            java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> attributesAssociations,
                                            java.lang.String datasetName,
                                            boolean removeExistingDatasets)
        Parameters:
        datasetNameOne - represents the first dataset to be joined
        datasetNameTwo - represents the second dataset to be joined
        attributesAssociations - represents a map of both datasets attributes. It is used to associate an attribute from one dataset to the other.
        datasetName - represents the name of the new dataset
        removeExistingDatasets - is a boolean indicating if the existing datasets must be removed. If true one of the datasets can be used to join the other.
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method joins two datasets into a single one. They can have different attributes and a map associates them. The join operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • updateDatasetValuesSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject updateDatasetValuesSync(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                                   java.lang.String attribute,
                                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> oldToNewValues)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - is the dataset name
        attribute - is the attribute that must be updated
        oldToNewValues - represents a map, associating the old values of the attribute with the new values to be updated.
        Returns:
        a JSON object with error or warning messages. In case of success, it returns the dataset URL inside the JSON object.
        Summary:
        This method updates some values of an attribute. The update operation is synchronous, this way the caller waits until it finishes.

      • await

        com.google.gson.JsonObject await(java.lang.String datasetURL)
        Parameters:
        datasetURL - is the dataset URL returned by asynchronous method calls of Learning Orchestra API
        Returns:
        a JSON object indicating if the dataset is projected correctly or not
        Summary:
        This method is responsible to lock the caller until a dataset is projected correctly into Learning Orchestra

      • deleteProjectionSync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject deleteProjectionSync(java.lang.String datasetName)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - represents the dataset name
        Returns:
        a JSON object with an error message, a warning message or a correct delete message
        Summary:
        This method is responsible for deleting the dataset. This delete operation is synchronous, so it locks the caller until the deletion finished. If a dataset was used by another task (Ex. projection, histogram, pca, tune and so forth), it cannot be deleted.

      • deleteProjectionAsync

        com.google.gson.JsonObject deleteProjectionAsync(java.lang.String datasetName)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - represents the dataset name
        Returns:
        a JSON object with an error message, a warning message or a correct delete message
        Summary:
        This method is responsible for deleting the dataset. This delete operation is asynchronous, so it does not lock the caller until the deletion finished. Instead, it returns a JSON object with a URL for a future use. The caller uses the URL for delete checks. If a dataset was used by another task (Ex. projection, histogram, pca, tune and so forth), it cannot be deleted.

      • searchAllProjections

        com.google.gson.JsonObject searchAllProjections()
        Returns:
        all datasets metadata stored in Learning Orchestra or an empty result
        Summary:
        This method retrieves all datasets metadata, i.e., it does not retrieve the dataset content.

      • searchProjectionContent

        com.google.gson.JsonObject searchProjectionContent(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                                   int pageSize,
                                                   int currentPage)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - is the name of the dataset
        pageSize - is the number of tuples or registers returned per page. It is an optional parameter. If not present, the page size will be 20 tuples/registers.
        currentPage - is the page where the search will start. It is an optional parameter. If not present, the search operation will start from page zero.
        Returns:
        a page with some tuples or registers inside or an error if there is no such dataset. The current page is also returned to be used in future content requests.
        Summary:
        This method is responsible for retrieving pages of the dataset content

      • searchProjectionContent

        com.google.gson.JsonObject searchProjectionContent(java.lang.String datasetName)
        Parameters:
        datasetName - is the name of the dataset
        Returns:
        a page with the first 20 tuples or registers inside or an error if there is no such dataset.
        Summary:
        This method is responsible for retrieving the dataset content, precisely the first 20 tuples
